http://pub175.ezboard.com/utamadortheassassin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tamador the Assassin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/1/02 5:37:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=695.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> One Rogue vs Ten People, Share experiences?</span><hr size=1> Hello everyone.  This will be my first duel ever.  Sorry if the title was misleading, I'm not going to be fighting ten people at the same time hehe.  I will be fighting a total of ten, or maybe a couple more, individually at different times.  Here's my magelo profile so you can see where I'm at equipment wise.<br><br><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112237">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112237</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><br>I will be purchasing the proper resist gear (2x BD Bracers, 2x BD Earrings, 2x Vel Diamond Rings, RBF, Frog Crown) as well as several pumice stones.  I've read up on the pvp information in the library and memorized alot of the important tips and strategies to be used.  I am Lvl 60 and will be dueling against (* means he/she has an epic) a 55 druid*, 55 pally*, 54 bard*, 54 shaman*, 53 enchanter, 53 warrior, 53 pally, 55 enchanter, 52 druid, 55 necro.  Please be aware that they are from a roleplaying guild so their equipment isn't uber.  The 55 druid* and the 55 pally* are the only two of the bunch that I am worried about because they are on more than the others and thus have more exprience in playing their class.  The 55 druid* however, hates to kite and never has kited anything much so I'm thinking that's a good thing<br><br>The library gave me basic information about how to duel.  What I want is to hear the knowledge other rogues may have gained from dueling one or more of these classes.  My friend informed me that because I was 60 and they were 55 and lower, they will have some difficulty landing their spells on me, especially if my mr is 100+ unbuffed.  I am definitely going to get Chaotic Stab before I begin the duels to give myself a bigger punch against the melees.<br><br>The duels will be one on one as I mentioned earlier and should be done in the Arena in the Bazaar or the Arena in Lake Rathe, not quite sure yet.  But I assure you it won't be in some random zone, it will definitely be in some arena.  Know that pretty much all ten people, like me, have never been in a serious duel like this so we are all inexperienced. <br><br>So, if other rogues could post the experiences they've had at fighting these different classes, or add in more words of wisdom for me to keep in mind, or even strategies and tactics you found helpful, please do.  Thanks again.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> EDIT</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Forgot to mention.  I won't be dueling them in any particular order.  I'll just be picking one and killing him.  This isn't a competition, it's actually a roleplaying event, one which they are only slightly aware of.  I will be calling them one at a time to wherever I want to do the duel and when they come in, I'll already be s/h and begin from there.  I only have to kill each of them once, get a screen shot of their corpse and that's that.  My goal is to kill them all once, then that's that.   <p><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112237">Veteran Tamador</a></b> the Feir'Dal Assassin<br><b>60th Seasoned Rogue</b> - Innoruuk<br></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/utamadortheassassin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tamador the Assassin</A> at: 7/1/02 6:00:39 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ukuspin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kuspin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/1/02 9:17:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=695.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: One Rogue vs Ten People, Share experiences?</span><hr size=1> Well due to the level difference, using something like the snare 4 poison (sloth) which is makable with bought components in Firiona vie will probably guarentee you a number of easy kills, and probably would be handy to reapply in the fight against the bard who might spend alot of time running out of reach.  Though it might have trouble sticking on the necro if he's floating.  A good shaman damage shield potion can also be handy for killing off pets very fast if your being led around while it beats on you, and of course sow potions always give the important mobility edge.  Enjoy the slaughter <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/udougiefresh007.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dougiefresh007</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/2/02 12:53:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=695.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> !</span><hr size=1> rogues werent made to rush 10 people...  wars were anyways you will die in like 2 seconds vs 10 people trust me<br><br><I>Edit: Sig way too big -Glip</i> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uglipthegnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glip the Gnome</A> at: 7/6/02 5:56:40 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uclearrain.showPublicP