r>   Necro - Dont bother with poison here ... if he uses dmf, you wont land it on him. Dont let him cast, he will have around 1600 hp or so, just beat it out of him while he tries to dot you. Necros are same as druids dont let him live to long. Dont pay att to the pet, just got for him and beat him down. If he uses shadow step you could have problems. Just try not to let him cast it.<br><br> <br>   You will win all of these duels, its not hard, just think about every single thing they can do and be aware, then again ... they are not 60 so you have the + since you will resist alot of spells just because you are higher. <br>    Use disspell before you land your poison, keep a few stacks of bandages in your bags and use poisons if you can. Even the easiest poison - spine break will make a big diff in those duels since the targets are lower lvl and the poison will stick for full time. <br><br>  Veteran Keliur T'Soul<br>   Ec'I <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufilash.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Filash</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/15/02 8:35:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=695.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: One Rogue vs Ten People, Share experiences?</span><hr size=1> For the love of all that is good don't use a mana drain on a 55 paladin. Or attempt to reapply poison in the middle of an arena duel. <p><a href="http://pub175.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselibraryreadonly.showMessage?topicID=114.topic">Rogue PvP Guide</a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufilash.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Filash</A> at: 7/15/02 8:36:24 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35